<collectionCode id="76B5EBBCE33AFFD4FC0BFDF39194FDB1" box="[934,1016,514,538]" country="New Zealand" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34070" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34070" name="New Zealand Arthropod Collection" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="Other institutional type">NZAC</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFDB0934DFD11" blockId="17.[192,1440,577,698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFDB09063FDF2" bold="true" box="[192,527,577,601]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Geographic distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="889F6FFCE33AFFD4FDB2FDB3901BFDF1" box="[543,631,578,602]" captionStart="Figures 89–94" captionStartId="71.[192,287,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,192,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-47@71.[192,1440,192,1857]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="Figures 89–94. Species distribution maps. 89) Bembidion maorinum maorinum. 90) B. musae. 91) B. nesophilum. 92) B. orbiferum. 93) B. parviceps. 94) B. puponga new species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181792" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181792/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
). North Island: WI–Santoft Forest (Koitiata Stream mouth). 
<collectionCode id="76B5EBBCE33AFFD4FACCFDB397FDFDF2" box="[1377,1425,578,601]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">WN</collectionCode>
– Kuku Beach (near Levin) [=Kuku Beach Road end beach]. Lake Waiorongomai Stream mouth. Titahi Bay. South Island: 
<collectionCode id="76B5EBBCE33AFFD4FE06FD7393BBFD31" box="[427,471,642,666]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">NN</collectionCode>
–Puponga Forest [=Farm] Park (Green Hills Stream mouth; Wharariki Stream mouth).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BE20F2E33AFFD4FF6DFD139690FB91" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFD13918EFCF1" blockId="17.[192,1440,738,858]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFD139342FD51" bold="true" box="[192,302,738,762]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Ecology</emphasis>
. Coastal lowland. Fossorial. Banks of meandering estuarine streams (
<quantity id="D75CDE9CE33AFFD4FB31FD139684FD52" box="[1180,1256,738,762]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 m</quantity>
wide) running through sand dunes (
<figureCitation id="889F6FFCE33AFFD4FE60FCF3905AFCB1" box="[461,566,770,794]" captionStart="Figures 111–112" captionStartId="76.[192,288,1875,1897]" captionTargetBox="[342,1303,255,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-48@76.[192,1440,192,1872]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figures 111–112. Species habitats, Bembidion (Zecillenus). 111) Hawkes Bay (HB), Waimarama, B. waimarama new species. 112) Nelson (NN), Puponga Farm Park, B. puponga new species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181802/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
), just above the highest tidal line, at a certain distance (
<quantity id="D75CDE9CE33AFFD4FAA8FCF39738FCB1" box="[1285,1364,770,794]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 m</quantity>
) from water. Open ground; wet, sandy (white, black), bare soil. Nocturnal; hides during the day in the sand. Gregarious. Occurs in association with staphylinids (
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FCE1FCB391BBFCF1" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[844,983,834,858]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFC70973FFC11" blockId="17.[192,1440,897,954]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFC709344FC32" bold="true" box="[192,296,897,921]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: September, December, March. Tenerals: December, March. Occasionally infested with fungi (Laboulbeniales). Defence mechanism: when alarmed, the adult escapes by running.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFC1097CDFC51" blockId="17.[192,1441,993,1018]" box="[192,1441,993,1018]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFC1093F1FC51" bold="true" box="[192,413,993,1018]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Brachypterous (incapable of flight). Fast runner. Vagility limited by flight incapacity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFBD09690FB91" blockId="17.[192,1276,1057,1082]" box="[192,1276,1057,1082]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFBD09381FB92" bold="true" box="[192,493,1057,1081]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Collecting techniques</emphasis>
. Pouring water over the ground; treading the soil with the feet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BE20F2E33AFFD4FF6DFB9393D2FAD1" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="101B7379E33AFFD4FF6DFB9393D2FAD1" blockId="17.[192,1440,1122,1402]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FF6DFB939350FBD1" bold="true" box="[192,316,1122,1146]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="CF1FCDDBE33AFFD4FD4FFB93917BFBD1" box="[738,791,1122,1146]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
locality, Puponga Farm Park. 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FB08FB9397CCFBD2" authorityName="Larochelle &amp; Lariviere" authorityYear="2015" box="[1189,1440,1122,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puponga">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FB08FB9397CCFBD2" box="[1189,1440,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Bembidion puponga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FDBCFB7390F7FB31" baseAuthorityName="Brookes" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[529,667,1154,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tillyardi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FDBCFB7390F7FB31" box="[529,667,1154,1178]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">B. tillyardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to diagnostic characters of the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FA28FB739346FB12" authorityName="Larochelle &amp; Lariviere" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puponga">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FA28FB739346FB12" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">B. puponga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the following distinguishing features: head and pronotum black or piceous; elytra pale testaceous with a reduced brownish irregular discal marking and interval 2 infuscated behind middle; legs pale testaceous with apex of femora and base of tibiae slightly infuscated; abdomen piceous; elytra with intervals subdepressed on disc and subapical sinuations moderately strong. 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FB04FAF397CCFAB2" authorityName="Larochelle &amp; Lariviere" authorityYear="2015" box="[1193,1440,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puponga">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FB04FAF397CCFAB2" box="[1193,1440,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Bembidion puponga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the southwestern North Island (WI, WN) and northwestern South Island (NN, Puponga Farm Park) while 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE33AFFD4FE32FAB3904AFAF1" baseAuthorityName="Brookes" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[415,550,1346,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tillyardi">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE33AFFD4FE32FAB3904AFAF1" box="[415,550,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">B. tillyardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to a single locality from the northwestern South Island (NN, 
<collectingRegion id="D260BD9BE33AFFD4FF6DFA939374FAD1" box="[192,280,1378,1402]" country="New Zealand" name="Nelson" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Nelson</collectingRegion>
, Tahunanui).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
